drill

1. Go back through and write a comment on what each line does.
2. Read each one backward or out loud to find your errors.
3. From now on, when you make mistakes, write down on a piece of paper what
kind of mistake
you made.
4. When you go to the next exercise, look at the mistakes you have made and try
not to make them
in this new one.
5. Remember that everyone makes mistakes. Programmers are like magicians who
fool everyone
into thinking they are perfect and never wrong, but itâ€™s all an act. They make
mistakes all the
time.
